<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-09-08T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-09-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="903" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d903">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.672(1929)/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Angora</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-08T18:00:00+02:00">September 8, 1929—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 8—5:10 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>5. I have begun negotiations for Treaty of Commerce and Navigation and
                            shall postpone leave of absence until they are completed. Expect to
                            cable Turkish counter proposals within a day or two. The proposed
                            Turkish alterations in Department’s text appear to be chiefly
                            clarifications and precisions rather than matters of principle.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>